.Says A New Anambra Beckons Anambra State Governor-elect Prof Chukwuma Charles Soludo has extended a special New Year greetings to the people of Anambra State and Nigerians in general. In his New Year message to Ndi Anambra, made available to the media by Mr. Joe Anatune, Head of Soludo Media Office, the Governor-elect said the out-going year was a mixed-grill of challenges and blessings. Obiano Grants 10% Tax Reduction To Anambra Citizens BREAKING: Soludo Wins Again As Court Dismisses Suit Challenging… Soludo said the security challenges and loss of precious lives witnessed towards the tail-end of the year were regrettable and very unfortunate. He added that the advent of the deadly Omicron variant of the COVID-19 pandemic further exacerbated the pains and suffering of Nigerians and people across the world as it impacted negatively on the world economy and businesses. On the positive side, Cee Cee Soludo said the successful conduct of the Anambra State governorship election, which was adjudged as the freest, fairest and most credible election in the nation’s democratic history, rekindled hope and confidence in the people who overwhelmingly voted for him as the next governor of Anambra State He commended the tenaciousness, resilience and never-die spirit of the average Ndi-Anambra, assuring that a greater Anambra beckons with a prosperous homeland where every Ndi Anambra will have a sense of fulfillment in their chosen areas of endeavour in life The Governor-elect further said he looks forward to March 17, 2022 when he would formally be sworn into office as the Executive Governor of Anambra State to begin the task of consolidating on the gains of Governor Willie Obiano administration. POLL He equally commended the incumbent governor for impacting positively on the lives of the people of Anambra state in the past 7 years Cee Cee Soludo therefore wished every Ndi-Anambra and Nigerians alike a glorious and prosperous New Year in 2022.